products.title: [In stock] pixelspace studio x KBDfans Endless-80 Mechanical Keyboard DIY KIT
products.body_html:
Start date: June 5th, 2021

 Inspiration

    "ENDLESS-80", yes, it is a spaceship that travels through the endless universe. This is the original intention of the author of "pixelspace studio" when designing this kit. The author is a science fiction fan. He is interested in all kinds of science fiction works, so the overall style of the kit is more "sci-fi" and "cyberpunk". The team spent 4 months on the front side RGB lighting effect,  in order to make it look cooler and more connotative. For the light trough of the CAPS lamp, the team also select plenty of different kinds, and finally chose this kind of retro PC design to fit the overall package. The overall style, "A gift from the future", it is a gift from the future!

Specs

  • Top Mount
  • The typing angle: 5 degree
  • Layout: 80% TKL Layout, the solder PCB support multiple layouts (7U space bar, 6.25U space bar, ISO enter keys), Hot-swap PCB only support 7U space bar
  • The PCB support QMK/VIA
  • The RGB Light Diffuser is designed for Caps lock

Include

  • Aluminum top and bottom case x1
  • Aluminum type-c cover X1
  • Aluminum nameplate x1
  • Aluminum painted weight bar x1
  • Aluminum light slot x1
  • 5MM Aluminum(Brass,PC) Plate x1
  • 6mm Hot-swap PCB x1
  • PCB for RGB x1
  • Polished acrylic LGP(light guide plate) x1
  • Acrylic black light covers x1
  • 4MM PORON foam x1
  • 3MM PORON foam x1
  • RGB Light Diffuser x3
  • Silicone rubber feet x 5

Specification for RGB lights

  • FN+end= RGB switch
  • FN+Space bar= RGB light mode switch
  • FN+↑↓= RGB light brightness adjustment
  • FN+←→= RGB light hue adjustment
  • FN+pgup/pgdn= Light saturation adjustment

Software link: QMK; VIA

products.body_html:
The Set Name is Agent, Secret Agent.

The day I watched my favorite movie series for the 7th time I realized I had to make a keycap set out of the colors, so here we are:

This set is inspired by a suit from a golden movie of my favorite agent. Ever since I was a kid, I've been a big fan of agents.
I have my own collections of gadgets and exhibits and wanted to create my own keycap set together with this agent theme. I am so proud to share my progress with you today.

products.body_html:
• Group Buy Date: would be updated later
  • Estimated shipping date: will be announced after the GB ends
  • PBT material
  • Dye-sub (The red and blue keys are reverse dye-sub)

 

The Inspiration

This set was inspired by the colours of the main character of an anime-style music video, for one of my favourite songs (Shelter), by one of my favourite artists (Porter Robinson)!

I wanted the set to capture her hair, dress and room with the light & dark pink alphas and mods, while the accent of blue captures the pale, empty sky that usually surrounds her. This is my first set, but I really wanted to make sure I do the inspiration justice and create something for anyone who is a fan of the character, song, artist or just the colours themselves.
